1
00:00:06,297 --> 00:00:09,279
We have to follow the advice
of the mahājana.

2
00:00:09,279 --> 00:00:11,984
[Karma | Motive of Movement]

3
00:00:11,984 --> 00:00:18,786
… because both are the same 
in terms of external movement,

4
00:00:18,786 --> 00:00:25,978
but one is moving under the faithful plane,
under the advice of Guru and Vaiṣṇava.

5
00:00:25,978 --> 00:00:30,484
Sādhu, Śāstra, Guru, and Vaiṣṇava,
you’re moving in the faithful plane.

6
00:00:30,484 --> 00:00:36,806
So, you’re sheltered.
What you’re doing is akarmic, it’s divine,

7
00:00:37,187 --> 00:00:41,077
it will be nourishing, progressive;
it’s everything.

8
00:00:41,077 --> 00:00:45,498
It’s life giving—
eternally life giving.

9
00:00:45,498 --> 00:00:50,456
The same exact movements
for another reason are vikarma;

10
00:00:50,456 --> 00:00:56,105
it will take you down, will ruin you.
The same exact movements.

11
00:00:56,105 --> 00:01:00,789
So, where’s karma located?
Guru Mahārāj would say, “In the mind.”

12
00:01:00,820 --> 00:01:05,276
That’s the seat of karmic activity.
It’s not the action so much.

13
00:01:05,276 --> 00:01:09,440
That’s why in law 
when they have a …

14
00:01:09,626 --> 00:01:18,325
especially in the case of murder,
they will talk about intent.

15
00:01:18,935 --> 00:01:22,253
So, they have to establish
criminal intent,

16
00:01:22,253 --> 00:01:27,965
that there’s no doubt that someone
was murdered; they were killed.

17
00:01:27,965 --> 00:01:36,514
But they say that to determine guilt
and subsequent punishment,

18
00:01:36,514 --> 00:01:42,777
we need to interrogate the person,
find out what were they thinking,

19
00:01:42,777 --> 00:01:46,737
why did this happen,
what’s the cause behind it all.

20
00:01:46,737 --> 00:01:56,163
And when that’s determined, motive, intent,
then you can establish innocence or guilt.

21
00:01:56,789 --> 00:02:03,062
So, karma is actually like that.
It’s not as much the movement,

22
00:02:03,062 --> 00:02:06,003
but the motive 
for the movement.

